<br>
  Many seasons have I now tread this great world of Norrath and the moon above.  Though I have always prefered the solitude offered to me by the wilderness, I find myself amidst more and more evil in this land, much of it too powerful for I alone to confont.<br>
<br>
  With the recent discovery of the lost islands of Broken Skull Rock, I can feel a resurgance amongst the Tier'dal of Antonica.  They are plotting; gathering their forces.  For what, I am unsure, but I know that their plans will not bring peace to these troubled lands.  For too long, our dark cousins have remained to themselves.  But now, they emerge again from Neriak.  Shadow Knights of Innoruuk travel Greater Faydark, slaying Elven warriors and innocents alike.  Necromancers bring their undead armies to bear against the guardians of Felwithe.  Warriors and wizards assault the human outpost of High Keep on a regular basis.  The good citizens of Norrath live under a great shadow of hatred and fear.  And though I call no one place my home, I will protect the innocent and lend my blades and bow to those who champion a peaceful existance.<br>
<br>
  But I cannot fight this battle alone.....<br>
<br>
                                                - Camthelion Ciryaten<br>
                                                     Ranger of Tunare<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Hello all, I am a new character to FV, but not a new player.  After a few other servers and a few other characters here on FV, I've come full circle back to my Ranger roots.  After a couple of guild memberships, I've found that being a part of a team and family is the best way to go for me.  I've looked at a few of the established good/neutral guilds, and while they are all great guilds with great people, I would really like to take a guild in a different direction....well, maybe not a different direction entirely, but with emphasis on roleplaying.  Such as building guild rivalries and alliances, only grouping with other 'good' races/classes, etc.  I would like to eventually get to the point of open guild wars and such.  ( I really like dueling, but can't stand to go back to a non RP server )  I've been playing EQ close to a year now, and though I'm not an expert, I'm pretty confident that I have a firm grasp of game mechanics.  I'm looking for any 'good' race players that are also interested in the aspects listed above.  I would also ask that anyone interested have a least 6 months of experience with EQ and have a character level 15 or higher.  Ability and willingness to RP is a must, as I would like to keep ooc comments to a minimum.  I would also ask that your FV character be your 'main'.  I've been in guilds where many members were just alts for another character on another server, or another account.  I also ask ( I know, I'm asking alot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) that you be able to spend a good amount of time in game.  I'm not asking for 40 hours a week or anything, I just want the guild members to be around more than once or twice every 10 days. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
  Bottom line for the guild is to fight any form of evil, help out other guilds and individuals whenever possible, form a good in-game friendship, and most of all, HAVE FUN!<br>
<br>
  High Elves, Half Elves, Wood Elves, and Humans are welcome.  <br>
<br>
  This post is rather general in nature as I haven't sat down to brainstorm ideas completely as of yet.  But I would love to discuss particlars and hash out ideas with anyone who is interested or just has a good idea they would like to share.<br>
<br>
  If this sounds like what you are looking for, please leave a message here or contact Camthelion in game.<br>
<br>
  Thanks and happy hunting!<br>
<br>
  - Camthelion Ciryaten, Ranger of Tunare<br>
