<br>
I am Sir Loric Leondegrance, holy knight and defender of our Mother, Tunare. I have fought against the Darkness which spreads over the lands like a plague for the past 30 seasons. At one point, I led an organization called the Conclave of the Righteous which strove to bring light to this growing darkness. Unfortunately, the agents of the underworld had deceitfully laid a trap under a guise of a truce. As a result, I was captured and was made prisoner of the enemy.<br>
<br>
The time of my imprisonment was difficult. I cannot recount the numerous times my captors had tried to break my spirit and compel me to forsake my Mother. The tortures to my mind and body attempted to force my capitulation. The pain was excruciating. I was near submitting to the brainwashing and begging for a merciful end when She came to me.<br>
<br>
The tier'dal had surmised that transforming me into an agent of hate was never going to be successful. So they had decided that the best way to make good use of me was to give me as an offering to the ogres of Ogguk so to reinforce the alliance between the two peoples. I was to be the main course in a feast to celebrate the latest victory of the dark armies in a recent battle.<br>
<br>
I was bound by my arms and feet, and placed in a wagon which would carry me to my doom. Resigned to my fate, I began praying to the Mother, requesting that She give me the power to die well,and not to disgrace the blood of my peoples. Apparently, the Mother had decided that it was not my time to die. <br>
<br>
As the caravan was passing through the forests of the Eastern Commonlands, we were assaulted my a multitude of animals. Black bears, lions, snakes, even wolves began attacking the caravan. A pair of squirrels had worked their way up into the wagon I lay in, and began to gnaw on the bindings which restrained my hands and feet. Within moments, I was free and limping my way off the wagon and into the forest.<br>
<br>
Eventually, I made my way back to Felwithe, only to discover that the Conclave had diminished,with many losing faith in the Cause we had embraced. Save only a few loyal members remained....Lasgalen Lothir, Bellewyn, Whittle, and Talaysen. It was with this shocking discovery that I resolved to disband our organization, and seek out allies so that we may once again take the fight to our enemies.<br>
<br>
OOC: Hello Camthelion. I am interested in the guild you propose. Many of it's idea were those shared by the Conclave of the Righteous in the past. The Conclave was a great guild, yet I was unable to invest the amount of time necessary to enable it to flourish. I would be greatly interested in aiding you in the conception of this guild if you so desire, and would be an eager  applicant for membership after its creation. If you have any questions of comments on this matter, please either contact me in game or on this thread.<br>
<br>
